Come to one.. or more than one! Won't you please???
I will have the internet at home tomorrow!!!!

Turns out I've been ignoring LiveJournal. My bad.

I was going to go on myspace again like usual but this computer at work is having an issue with it at the moment. Ah well.

All moved in! Yay! Everything is unpacked except downstairs bathroom stuff. But that's only because we have nowhere to put anything.

Our last show went very well. I thought we sounded great. It's weird to be trying out drummers. No one is really standing out yet but hopefully we'll find someone soon. We just got booked for a show February 28th at Studio 7 with Ruxton Towers and some other awesome bands. We're also still booked for January 28th at Hansen's with The East End!

The housewarming party went very well. It was a lot of fun. Not a whole lot of people, but just enough of the cool ones.

There is NOTHING to do at work. I did one order today.. and stuffed and sealed some envelopes. Been on lunch for an hour.. I think we're all leaving soon because there is nothing to do it's rediculous. I wish it didn't take me so long to get home. Stupid bus.

It's really weird having Shaina be gone... and she's still going to be gone for like two weeks. I've gotten use to seeing her every day so having her not be around is VERY strange.

Our house is getting decorated quite quickly. Lots of quotes up on the walls, it's awesome. Comcast doesn't service our area though.. so we have to go with this company called Millennium who offers the same services but more movie channels for the same price. I'm excited about it.

Anyway..... I can't think of anything else to type about.. I think I'll be leaving here shortly. Woo.

peace out... or something..

Tomorrow will be our last show for a while, so please come if you can! We'll be playing first, and we're the only non-signed band on the bill. This is very important for us so please come show your support!! Our drummer Chris will be leaving after this show.

Alabaster
Ever We Fall
Lucky For Nothing
Morning Call
The Classic Crime

Sat Dec 10 2005
Studio 7
110 S Horton St
Seattle WA

Doors at 4:30, we go on at FIVE!

$6 advance, $8 at the door. See you there?

If you're not doing anything tonight, come out for a great night of ROCK at the Blue Moon Tavern in the U District featuring A Cold December Way, Dangermart, and my band, ALABASTER. The fun starts at 8pm, we are on stage second. The best part... it's FREE!! That's right, no cover! So come on out and enjoy the music. 21+, hope to see you there!!!

http://www.myspace.com/alabaster
http://www.ilovealabaster.com

I forget to write in here some times. So here is my update, in short. Shaina has been living in our apartment with us for the past couple weeks. We pretty much hang out every minute of every day, and I have found that I don't get tired of her. Ever. And that's good. I like having friends like that. Work has been hectic and somewhat annoying but I still enjoy my job lots. My car had some issues last week but my dad bought and installed a new alternator and it's fine again. Band stuff is awkward (I don't wanna talk about it) but still going good. We are in the process of writing 2 new songs...one of which is fucking AMAZING and is going to be so awesome once it's finished. Our drummer Chris informed us the other night that he's going to move home in January and go back to school so he'll no longer be with us... and he's going to help us find a new drummer as well. Also, we have a free show tomorrow night at the Blue Moon Tavern in the U District. 21+ obviously, FREE! 8pmish. We go on second out of 3 bands. We also just got booked for a show on Saturday December 10 at Studio 7 playing with The Classic Crime, Ever We Fall, Lucky For Nothing, and Morning Call. All these bands are signed to major labels. This show should be an amazing opportunity for us. Also, we have a hookup who does booking for Warped Tour and might get us a couple dates on next year's tour. And soon we may have airplay on a radio station in the NETHERLANDS. Amazing. Today is Thanksgiving! Erin and I are at her parents house to pick up some things. We ate at my parents house and I am as stuffed as a turkey. I've practiced driving today. Drove to my parents house, and to Erin's parents from my parents. Soon will drive to Ballard to go to see RENT :) What else... OH RIGHT we're moving this weekend. Paying first month's rent on Saturday.. and starting to move stuff into our HOUSE! I can't even believe it. Shaina's room
Bathroom
Me, Erin, Liz in the living room
Front door, downstairs door, closet in living room
Kitchen
Liz's room
Mine and Erin's room
Mine and Erin's room
Mine and Erin's closet
Mine and Erin's room
Downstairs bathroom/laundry room
Room inbetween mine and Erin's room and Liz's room
Living room
Erin in the living room
Have to be out of our apartment in ONE WEEK. Weird. I hope we can do it!!!

Let's talk about how hot Tegan from Suicide Girls is...

http://podcast2.suicidegirls.com/media/video/SG_Tegan_2005-10-19.m4v

HOTTTTTTTTTTT
So I was just looking through new interviews on http://www.bassgirls.com...... SUZI QUATRO has an interview. I have an interview on the same site as Suzi Quatro. That's fucking awesome.

So, good news! After much waiting, our recording of our new song, Far From Okay, is now available for your listening pleasure at http://www.myspace.com/alabaster!

Please keep in mind that this recording does not at all do this song justice. You have to see it live to experience the awesomeness of it. I seriously am so in love with this song, and I can't even explain it. It's just.. powerful. So PLEASE go check it out.

And PLEASE come see us tomorrow. 4:30pm. $7 advance, $9 at the door. It's going to be an awesome show, we are all very pumped for it.


In other news, everything is still going great. Yesterday after work, Shaina and I were so tired that we took a 3 hour nap. She came over tonight after band practice before she headed up to Liz's and we made gingerbread cookies, and then her, Erin and I fell asleep for 3 hours. I wasn't even really tired but I was laying in between Shaina and Erin... I had my left arm around Erin and Shaina was pretty much clutching my right arm... so my only option was to lay there so they were both comfortable. Then I fell asleep. Go figure.

Man I am so excited about the show tomorrow, it's going to be AWESOME. After that, sleepover night! And then on Sunday we go pay our deposit for the house!!!! I think we might be signing the lease then too. Everything is working out quite well. Our new address will be 3716 14th Ave S, Seattle WA 98144! Yay yay yay!!!

I really need to head to bed now.... later!!

Hey everyone!!! We are playing this Saturday at Studio 7 with great local bands The Art of Self Defense and Truce as well as Vaeda from Burbank CA. This is an early show, and it starts at 4:30pm. Tickets are $7 from any band member (buy them from us ASAP!) before the show, or are $9 at the door. If you are planning to buy a ticket from us, you need to get a hold of us before 1:30pm on Saturday. Details at our MySpace or our website. Hope to see you there!!! xoxo Kate, Chris, Shaina, Joe and Jen Alabaster

Oh yea and I found Marc and Ryan's new band (they were my old bandmates)...

http://www.myspace.com/deferredsuccessband

Man they hurt my ears. And they re-used 3 of our old songs. I can't even explain how angry that makes me. I know that they wrote those songs, but they were Half Past Two songs. You don't do shit like that. Bastards.

Oh well at least my band is good. ;)

Yikes. I haven't been able to write lately because my computer has had nothing but issues. Telling me I couldn't connect to the internet. How rude!!! But everything works now. Thank goodness.

Working with Shaina is great. I haven't had to ride a bus in over a week now! Plus I always have someone to talk to.

Sunday we went to look at a house. We filled out applications and paid the application fee... and today, we got the house! WE GOT A HOUSE!!! It's a rental house, obviously. It's $1095 a month for 3 bedrooms, 1 1/2 bath, full size washer and dryer, water, sewer and garbage included in the rent. $600 deposit, $100 per pet. AMAZING! December 1st, we will live there. It's in Beacon Hill... like at 14th and Spokane St. It's connected to another house, but you'd never know being inside of it. So finally Erin and I will be living with Shaina and Liz which will be so much more conveinient for all of us since we hang out all the time anyway :) Working with Shaina has also helped me realize that I don't get tired of her at all! We're totally BFFs. Hehe.

So we seriously need to start packing.. ASAP.

The band isn't playing in Portland anymore. Something happened with the booker and they went with Portland bands instead. Which kinda sucks, but it's okay. I was scared about how we'd do two nights in a row. But practice has been sounding really good lately. With the exception of my amp... which has a buzzing speaker :( And today I broke ANOTHER bass string. This is the third one in like 4 months. I changed all my strings and hopefully this won't happen again for a long time. I'm sad I wasted so much money on those Dean Markley strings that were supposed to last forever. Oh well. More importantly I need to figure out what's wrong with my amp. Luckily I have a 2 year warranty on the speakers.

Anyway so we are still playing on the 12th at Studio 7. Doors at 4 or 4:30. We play first. We have advance tickets available for $7. Or they are $9 day of show. But you should buy them from us because you love us like that :) 

http://www.ilovealabaster.com
http://www.myspace.com/alabaster
http://www.garageband.com/artist/alabasterband
http://www.purevolume.com/alabaster
http://www.isound.com/alabaster
- and most importantly, read my interview at -
http://www.bassgirls.com!

Wow it turns out I'm really tired! Night!!!!

Wow I sure haven't been writing lately... too preoccupied with other things I suppose. I've been a busy bee lately.

Thursday was our show at the J&M. It went really well aside from my amp sounding funny, and Joe's amp cord fucking up. And me messing up a few times. Other than that, it was real good. That Saturday we played at the A Lesson In Chaos Halloween house party. It was actually really cool. My Ron Burgundy Halloween costume didn't really turn out the way I had hoped... I think I looked more like a mix of Charlie Chaplin and Hitler, unfortunately. The main problem was the wig we bought didn't work out, so we dyed my hair... but we didn't have brown hair dye so we dyed it black. Ah well. We played really well. We didn't bring my amp since it's been rattling... so I got to play through ALC's 8x10 Ampeg bass amp. Freakin awesome that thing is.

After we played, Erin, Liz, Shaina and I drove to Liz's to get her toothbrush and L Word DVDs and then went to Walmart in our costumes. Shaina was a hot cowgirl, Erin was a bee. Liz was just hot :) We got some movies and then headed home for our weekly sleepover. 

Sunday we got up to go house hunting but ate at Old Country Buffet first. I accidentally bumped into Liz and knocked her plate out of her hand and she burned her finger really bad on the mashed potatoes. Poor Liz!!! After eating we tried to look at some houses but people don't like to call us back, so we didn't see ANYTHING! After that we went to Blockbuster and got Soul Survivors. We really only wanted to watch because of Eliza Dushku but that movie made no sense whatsoever!! Weird. Then we watched Coyote Ugly, 40 Days and 40 Nights, The Upside of Anger and the Ellen DeGeneres Here and Now special. Then we all went to sleep. Shaina woke up at 2am and quit her job at UPS. She also applied at my work that day. They are against hiring friends but they were desperate for people immediately.

Anyway, Shaina came over last night and we watched Sleepy Hollow. Well we watched parts of it. Fell asleep in the middle of it. After it was over she headed up to Liz's to spend the night. She got up early this morning and came to pick me up and we headed to work together for her first day! I got about 4 small orders done and aside from that just worked on the GameTime and Element orders that need to go out asap. Evelyn, another new girl Collin hired started today too, around 2pm. She seems really cool. And tomorrow a girl who works at Toys in Babeland is starting work. Amazing. Josh also hired the girl with tattoos on her neck to be our new sales rep and she is HOTT. She walked into the room and was like "hey" to Shaina and she was like oh my god. Seriously... it's too bad she's in her own office all day with no one to stare at her :)

After work Shaina dropped me off. I've been bored ever since I got home cuz Erin is working late and there is nothing to do really. Shaina will probably be heading over pretty soon though, at least for a couple hours. Then she might stay at Liz's again. And then come back to pick me up in the morning to head to work.

And there is my update for the past week!

We are continuing in our pattern of getting booked for shows left and right!!! Oct 27 2005 8:30P J&M's (Pioneer Square) 21+ Seattle, WA with A Chance Without and Oscar's Mad ($5) Oct 29 2005 8:00P Halloween Spook Fest~~~~~~~>House Party Tukwila, WA with A Lesson In Chaos and Spent Nov 11 2005 7:00P Paris Theater (supporting Vaeda) Portland, OR with Vaeda and Stu's Shoes ($8) Nov 12 2005 6:30P Studio 7 (supporting Vaeda) Seattle, WA with Vaeda, Truce and The Art of Self Defense ($7/$9) Nov 25 2005 9:00P Blue Moon Tavern (U-District) 21+ Seattle, WA with Dangermart ($5) Dec 16 2005 8:00P JA Michaels Port Orchard, WA with The Black Light District ($5) Jan 28 2006 8:00P Hansens 21+ Bremerton, WA with The East End ($5)

Northern State again! I got to the Croc before the girls did. I walked to Westlake and back, waited outside for a little bit, and then went in to order some food. Got a french dip. Delicious. The girls showed up right as I finished. Sprout was driving their van and waved as they parked. Spero was wearing her shirt. They came in and said hello. Sprout gave me a hug. I sat while they set up. Sprout walked by to head to the bathroom and when she came back I was stretching. She asked if I was alright and I told her I was sore and she started rubbing my shoulders. Her dad's a chiropracter so she knew what she was doing. I'm very tense!! They did sound check, a couple interviews, and then it was show time. The first band was Optimus Rhyme who were amazing!! One of my new favorites. I bought their CD (I left it at work today though!) Up next was No-Fi Soul Rebellion who were very entertaining and I'd like to see them again. Then, Northern State. They mentioned my birthday, and thanked me for the shirts on stage. Amazing. Got some awesome pics, and some cool videos too. I'd write more but I really need to go to sleep!

Absolutely amazing and more...

Liz and I left my house around 2, went to the bank, picked up Shaina, and were on our way to Portland. We made one stop on the way there, in Vader, at a gas station/Subway. Got food, left. Got to the Crystal Ballroom around 6. Waited in line for an hour, saw Angie, Kimba, and Allison. Random! Got inside, got a great spot right in front of the stage on the right side.

The first band, the Hot IQ's were very good. They had a kickass girl drummer. They sounded a lot like Hot Hot Heat.

Then, Northern State. I sang along with ALL the words. They noticed. They kept looking at me, pointing at me, winking at me, and came over to shake my hand. And they kept mentioning about how I obviously had the CDs. Amazing. Got some awesome pics thanks to it. After their set I gave them the shirts I made for them like a year ago. I gave them straight to Spero, and she absolutely loved it!! She was like "This is so awesome, I think I might cry!" They were all astounded that I had the sleeves be their favorite colors.. except I did that on purpose, because I asked Sprout what their favorite colors were. Spero said she would probably wear hers at the Seattle show since she's out of clean clothes.

And then, Tegan and Sara. Amazing as always. They both seemed in bad moods though, but that's probably because they've been on tour PRACTICALLY all year long. New drummer Johnny is not bad. I still miss Rob.. but he did good. I know what it's like to come into a band that's been together for quite some time and have to learn all the songs and play them live. So I have compassion for him. I only noticed him mess up a couple of times. Ted was super cute as always, and Chris just stood there like usual. He looked at me funny when they were playing Walking With A Ghost, because Liz, Shaina and I were so uninterested in singing it because we do not like that song anymore. Then he laughed. I always find it funny when Chris laughs because he always has the same look on his face.

They played My Number... which in all the times I've seen them live, I've never heard them play. Shaina gave a CD to new drummer Johnny after the show. He said he'd take a listen and hand it off to the girls. Let's hope he does :)

We headed over to the merch table afterwards and Hesta Prynn came up to me, wearing the shirt I made and asked "Did you make this?" Amazing. Talked to them at the merch table for a little bit. Sprout gave me a button... which is apparently the only new item of merch they have. I didn't see sweatshirts but I hope they have them tomorrow because I reallllly want one. Shaina and Liz now love Northern State. I'm trying to convince Shaina to come with me tomorrow so I don't have to go alone. I wish Liz could go but she already had to pretend be sick to come to this show.

Poor Shaina though... she works the early shift at UPS, from 3:30-8:30. I don't know what she decided on but I know when we left Portland she was contemplating not going in. The only sleep she would get would be in the car. And she was up since 2:45am! She worked at UPS yesterday and then got called into Starbucks so she didn't get to take a nap. How she made it through the entire show I have no idea. She is a super trooper.

I got cramps when we were almost to Portland so that sucked a lot. They are just now starting to go away thanks to the ibuprofen I took. And the bath I took.

Anyway I need to resize these pictures and go to bed. I am exhausted!!!

Holy shit a bike!

Holy crap a bike!

Goo goo gah gah bikey...


Sorry we watched Dickie Roberts yesterday. I do enjoy that movie.

ANYWAY in more important news IT'S MY BIRTHDAY!!! In 39 more minutes it will be my exact birth time. 1:54am. 23 years old. Weird.

Going to dinner with my parents and Erin tomorrow at Joey's on Lake Union. Very excited. Very good food.

I wonder what I'm getting for my birthday... hmmm...

So the show we're scheduled to play in Portland...tickets are being sold on Ticketmaster. I'd say that's pretty cool. Yay. Big, good bands too. Damn right. Bed time, I have to wake up and go to work tomorrow...er... today. And then the day after that is my birthday! YAY!!!

Sooooooooooooooo it's very strange... my birthday is in three days and it sure doesn't feel like it's coming up. 

I'm going to be 23.

Such a weird age. Right between 20 and 25. An awkward time I think... kind of like being 19. Already 18 but not quite 21.

To celebrate, Erin and my parents and I are going out to dinner on my birthday. The next day, Liz, Shaina and I are driving down to Portland to see Northern State and Tegan and Sara. Day after that, Northern State will be at the Crocodile and I will be first in line.

Tonight is continuing on with a new ritual... where Liz and Shaina spend the night, and the four of us (Liz, Shaina, Erin and I) spend our Sunday looking for a house we can all rent. We are trying to think of a name for the house...but maybe that will come after we find the house. We found one last weekend that is just 13 blocks north and 2 blocks east. A cute little 3 bedroom. One bedroom is tiny... so we would make that the office. And we would make the dining room Shaina's room (she's dying to have a room that isn't really a bedroom). The guy that lives in the apartment downstairs from the house is very cool. He used to be a heavy metal drummer and now does jazz stuff, so he wouldn't have a problem with noise if there ever were any. As soon as Shaina mentioned we were in a band, he was very excited. I need to drop a CD off for him still.

Speaking of the band... I got recognized yesterday. I was at Suncoast and the guy behind the counter was like "You look familiar... are you in Alabaster?" I said "Yes I am" and he said "Bass player?" I said "Yup" He said "Jen, right?" It was very strange. It ended up being that he's in the band The Fizzgigs, who we played with at The Funhouse, but still it felt nice that someone recognized me. Still real weird.

And apparently yesterday, Shaina's friend Jess got a message on myspace from some girl who was like "How did you get a picture with Shaina from Alabaster? I'm so jealous!" Freakin weird.

I have to clean up the house cuz of course it's a sty again..which sucks because for a while there it was staying clean. Me having a job and being tired all the time from lifting isn't helping.

BUT I do still love my job. All the guys I work with are awesome. Scott is like a big teddy bear. I wish I knew a straight girl I could hook him up with. He's very sweet.

Anyway, off I go a cleaning.

Jesus, as if I didn't know Studio 7 was full of asses before, this just proves it further.

I posted a message on the message board asking why the site was never updated.

I received a reply today from admin saying this:

Hmmm good question. I just threw the latest poster up there?

I replied with this:

Hmm. First time I've seen anything new in quite some time. I was just curious.

I just got an email from them that read this:

When it comes to having bands listed, we can only post what outside promoters update us with... IF THEY DONT SEND US WHAT BANDS ARE PLAYING WE MOST CERTAINLY CANT POST THEM, NOW CAN WE!!

If you would like to contact me directly please email me at

******@studioseven.us

Thank you
******

Uhm WHAT? Can we say assholes? No one said you had to be bitchy, I was simply asking a question. How was I supposed to know that the promoters didn't send them show information? I wish I cared enough to boycott their stupid venue by not playing there anymore.. not like anyone ever shows up anyway... but I like playing shows so I'll just deal with. But seriously, why do they need to be asses about it? Give me a freakin break.

Kate put up some new pics on our myspace

http://www.myspace.com/alabaster


They are awesome. All the other new ones should be up on our site tomorrow

http://www.ilovealabaster.com


Looks like my band will be getting a show in Bremerton in January.
Upcoming dates:

10/28 - Tost - World Folk Battle of the Bands (maybe, no confirmation so far)
11/11 - Paris Theatre, Portland! - Playing with a band from Cali called Vaeda
11/12 - Studio 7 - Playing with Vaeda again
11/25 - Blue Moon Tavern - Day after Thanksgiving show
1/28 - Hansen's - Bremerton. Should be fun!

All my muscles hurt from all the lifting I've been doing. We are organizing the warehouse and it's pretty amazing how much we've gotten done. YAY!

House-hunting on Sunday. YAY!!!

Time for a shower!

We have a show in Portland!! November 11! And we have a show the day after with the same band. A two-day tour!! Amazing. I am so excited about this. We are playing with a band called Vaeda. Check them out at http://www.myspace.com/vaeda

More into the Bigtime Entertainment sucks ass story...

We got there at 5:40 last night, and apparently were the last band to arrive. The Bigtime Rep had already made the schedule and apparently couldn't change it. The only open slot was headlining. Now here are the mistakes Bigtime made:

1) They are trying to enfore a rule that you have to sell at least 35 tickets to the show in order to work with them in the future
2) We sold one ticket, were told it was fine, and were picked to have the headlining slot due to our tardiness.
3) The rep didn't even try to change the lineup, and we didn't get to play because Shaina had to be at work at 3:30 this morning
4) They do NOTHING to promote the shows
5) The bands have to print out the tickets, sell the tickets AND promote the show
6) What is the point of Bigtime? As far as I can tell, they get all the money from the ticket sales, and all they do is pick the bands, pick the date, and set it up at Studio 7.

Fucking REDICULOUS. I wish there was a better way to complain to them but they are horrible at answering emails and their website is barely ever updated.

I hate them.

Time to eat lunch now though before Jake comes back from lunch and steals his computer back!

Not playing tonight after all.

Bigtime Entertainment SUCKS ASS.

Reminder that my band is playing at Studio 7 tonight. We kicked ass at KTUB on Saturday and look forward to doing so again. Please try to come. Doors are at 6:20, we will probably play first (though I don't know 100%!)

That's right... my band is playing tonight at the Kirkland Teen Center. Please try to come out if you can!!! Doors are at 7pm, cost is $5 at the door. We will be going on second. Chains of Pain is first, then us, then Final Prayer, and then Netherelm. A bunch of metal bands and some Alabaster! Please come!!! Look forward to seeing you there!

So yesterday Liz and I were walking in Ballard back to her car from Sonic Boom and I ran into Bjorn, my old drummer. Apparently he just left the band, because they suck! They tried to record again and I guess it sounded like shit. So he said he just stopped going to practice after that. And in his own words "Marc never figured out that he sucked". Amazing. Best moment of my life. He also said that out of me, Ryan and Marc, I was the best at what I did. Stupid fucker Marc.. trying to tell me I'm not good enough. I knew Bjorn didn't feel that way.

It made my heart smile so big I can't even tell you.

The Stewie Untold Story DVD is very funny. Go get it ASAP.

Leaving for work soon. I'm tired! Can I take a nap when I get home? Probably not but we'll see...

Another day, another show confirmation. We now have FIVE shows coming up in the next 2 months.

Friday September 30 - Fall City house party (http://www.ilovealabaster.com for details on all shows)
